article_metadata.description: Local hospitals have to serve fewer uninsured patients as a result of Ohio’s expanded Medicaid program. To a lesser extent, subsidized private health coverage available through the new government-run insurance marketplace also has thinned the ranks of Ohio’s uninsured, though that coverage often comes with high deductibles that sometimes turn into bad debt for hospitals.
